</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="617" pageNumber="618" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="617" pageNumber="618">
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1847" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Chlaenius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="617" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevilabris">Chlaenius brevilabris</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1847: 437. Type locality: &quot;ad Insulam Longam NovEboraci [= Long Island, New York]&quot; (original citation). Three syntypes in MCZ [# 5864].
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="617" pageNumber="618">
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Chlaenius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="617" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consimilis">Chlaenius consimilis</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1847: 437 [
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="617" pageNumber="618">nomen dubium</emphasis>
]. Type locality: &quot;ad Rocky Mountains&quot; (original citation). Holotype [by monotypy] (♂) in MCZ [# 5865]. Synonymy established by Horn (1876d: 276). Note. According to Bell (1960: 143), the holotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Chlaenius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="617" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consimilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="617" pageNumber="618">Chlaenius consimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a deformed specimen that could be instead an abnormal 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Chlaenius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="617" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="617" pageNumber="618">Chlaenius tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="617" pageNumber="618">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1914" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Chlaenius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="617" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="texanellus">Chlaenius texanellus</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1914: 37. Type locality: &quot;Galveston [Galveston County], Texas&quot; (original citation). Nineteen syntypes in USNM [# 47712]. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="617" pageNumber="618">New synonymy</emphasis>
. Note. Bell (1960: 143) retained this name for a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1847" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Chlaenius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="617" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevilabris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="617" pageNumber="618">Chlaenius brevilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on different forebody metallic lustre; I believe the form does not warrant subspecific status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="618" lastPageNumber="619" pageId="617" pageNumber="618" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="617" pageNumber="618">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="618" lastPageNumber="619" pageId="617" pageNumber="618">
This species ranges from south-central New Hampshire (Merrimack County, Ross T. Bell pers. comm. 2008) to eastern South Dakota (Kirk and Balsbaugh 1975: 35), including southern Ontario (Lindroth 1969a: 987), south to southern Texas (Bell 1960: 143) and southwestern South Carolina (Hampton County, CMNH). 
<pageBreakToken pageId="618" pageNumber="619" start="start">The</pageBreakToken>
records from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Utah”">&quot;Utah&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Bousquet and Larochelle 1993: 207) and New Mexico (Fall and Cockerell 1907: 160) need confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
